1
00:00:03,310 --> 00:00:26,420
Saying this little phrase, he always says, the only one who likes change is a wet baby. And it's true, isn't it? Change is hard, but change is one of those things that we can count on in life. It is a constant in the world, and that is that things change.

2
00:00:27,900 --> 00:00:30,200
Professor and author Leonard Sweet wrote this.

3
00:00:30,280 --> 00:00:35,260
He said, I fully expect to wake up to an entirely different world

4
00:00:35,260 --> 00:00:38,460
than the one that I went to bed in the night before.

5
00:00:39,850 --> 00:00:42,790
He says, more changes now occur in one decade

6
00:00:42,790 --> 00:00:46,690
than occurred in entire centuries in the past.

7
00:00:47,630 --> 00:00:48,750
We see that, don't we?

8
00:00:49,990 --> 00:00:53,030
How many of you realize you went to bed last night

9
00:00:53,030 --> 00:00:55,770
and the war was in one direction

10
00:00:55,770 --> 00:01:01,030
and this morning they captured Saddam Hussein, just like that.

11
00:01:03,580 --> 00:01:06,920
Things can happen and turn on a dime.

12
00:01:09,440 --> 00:01:11,240
Life changes, doesn't it?

13
00:01:11,280 --> 00:01:14,540
Change is a constant in our world.

14
00:01:14,860 --> 00:01:18,100
We've seen a lot of changes this past year right here in our own church.

15
00:01:18,100 --> 00:01:21,840
A new governance document, new staff, new ministries.

16
00:01:22,160 --> 00:01:24,280
We welcome new members in our church.

17
00:01:25,500 --> 00:01:28,860
We say goodbye to others as they went home to be with Jesus.

18
00:01:28,860 --> 00:01:37,560
I read once that a church is not a static institution, but it is a living organism,

19
00:01:37,880 --> 00:01:40,020
and that it's always in flux.

20
00:01:41,420 --> 00:01:47,740
As each new person comes, or each new person leaves, we are constantly a different group

21
00:01:47,740 --> 00:01:53,980
of people, and in that sense, we have to, in essence, rejoin the church more or less

22
00:01:53,980 --> 00:01:57,960
every week, because we're never really the same.

23
00:01:58,800 --> 00:02:00,360
It's always changing.

24
00:02:01,980 --> 00:02:04,920
Many of you don't recognize your world today.

25
00:02:05,080 --> 00:02:07,720
It's not the same one that you grew up in.

26
00:02:08,550 --> 00:02:10,650
And I share that sentiment as well.

27
00:02:11,740 --> 00:02:18,740
As I travel to the high schools and the colleges and the seminaries and things as part of my own ministry,

28
00:02:18,740 --> 00:02:25,640
I realize how quickly that I have changed and things have changed even since I was there and it wasn't that long ago.

29
00:02:26,320 --> 00:02:27,180
Things are different.

30
00:02:27,300 --> 00:02:28,300
I don't know the language.

31
00:02:28,300 --> 00:02:29,580
I don't know the phrases.

32
00:02:29,820 --> 00:02:32,640
I don't know what's in or out.

33
00:02:34,500 --> 00:02:36,800
And change can overwhelm us.

34
00:02:36,940 --> 00:02:40,260
There can be a lot of challenges and change that can leave us breathless.

35
00:02:40,980 --> 00:02:47,480
And the reason I describe these realities is that this kinds of change and chaos and

36
00:02:47,480 --> 00:02:54,180
difficulty we might face in our world today is very similar to the kind of a world that

37
00:02:54,180 --> 00:03:05,890
Mary and Joseph experienced as well, for they too found themselves in a changing and a flux

38
00:03:05,890 --> 00:03:15,680
environment. Their country was under military occupation by the Roman Empire. Lots of uncertainty

39
00:03:15,680 --> 00:03:22,180
and concern amongst friends and family and countrymen. Politically, economically, it was not

40
00:03:22,180 --> 00:03:31,730
the most stable time. The Hebrew people had no control over their own future. There was no

41
00:03:31,730 --> 00:03:41,940
certainty about what was to come, no stability upon which to rely. And it doesn't say it in the

42
00:03:41,940 --> 00:03:48,180
text, but I suspect that tragedy and illness and death and financial worries, the kinds of things

43
00:03:48,180 --> 00:03:55,920
that we live with today, were also a part of their world as well. And I think that Mary and Joseph

44
00:03:55,920 --> 00:03:59,250
may have felt the same way we do today,

45
00:03:59,330 --> 00:04:02,750
a little uneasy, a little unsure, a little out of control,

46
00:04:03,090 --> 00:04:07,030
perhaps a little overwhelmed at all the things in their world.

47
00:04:08,500 --> 00:04:11,890
But then there was an unusual meeting.

48
00:04:14,940 --> 00:04:18,060
In the sixth month of Elizabeth's pregnancy,

49
00:04:18,280 --> 00:04:21,000
God sent the angel Gabriel to Nazareth,

50
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:24,660
a village in Galilee to a virgin named Mary.

51
00:04:25,720 --> 00:04:28,420
She was engaged to be married to a man named Joseph,

52
00:04:28,420 --> 00:04:30,640
a descendant of King David.

53
00:04:31,500 --> 00:04:33,200
Gabriel appeared to her and said,

54
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:34,700
Greetings, favored woman.

55
00:04:35,220 --> 00:04:37,100
The Lord is with you.

56
00:04:38,610 --> 00:04:40,150
Confused and disturbed,

57
00:04:40,950 --> 00:04:43,190
Mary tried to think what the angel could mean.

58
00:04:44,190 --> 00:04:47,330
Don't be frightened, Mary, the angel told her,

59
00:04:47,630 --> 00:04:50,370
for God has decided to bless you.

60
00:04:52,800 --> 00:04:54,980
You will become pregnant and have a son,

61
00:04:55,340 --> 00:04:56,980
and you are to name him Jesus.

62
00:04:57,940 --> 00:05:01,660
He will be very great and will be called the Son of the Most High,

63
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:05,440
and the Lord God will give him the throne of his ancestor David,

64
00:05:05,880 --> 00:05:08,540
and he will reign over Israel forever.

65
00:05:08,960 --> 00:05:11,120
His kingdom will never end.

66
00:05:12,960 --> 00:05:14,020
Mary asked the angel,

67
00:05:14,920 --> 00:05:17,640
But how can I have a baby? I'm a virgin.

68
00:05:18,700 --> 00:05:19,800
The angel replied,

69
00:05:19,900 --> 00:05:22,100
The Holy Spirit will come upon you,

70
00:05:22,100 --> 00:05:25,820
and the power of the Most High will overshadow you,

71
00:05:26,060 --> 00:05:28,540
so the baby born to you will be holy,

72
00:05:28,620 --> 00:05:30,860
and will be called the Son of God.

73
00:05:32,060 --> 00:05:36,400
What's more, your relative Elizabeth has become pregnant in her old age.

74
00:05:37,140 --> 00:05:41,580
People used to say she was barren, but she is already in the sixth month,

75
00:05:42,230 --> 00:05:45,450
for nothing is impossible with God.

76
00:05:47,030 --> 00:05:49,270
And Mary responded, I am the Lord's servant,

77
00:05:49,270 --> 00:05:52,530
and I am willing to accept whatever he wants.

78
00:05:53,230 --> 00:05:55,450
May everything you have said come true.

79
00:05:56,230 --> 00:05:57,570
And then the angel left.

80
00:05:59,280 --> 00:06:04,060
A few days later, Mary hurried to the hill country of Judea, to the town where Zechariah

81
00:06:04,060 --> 00:06:04,420
lived.

82
00:06:05,020 --> 00:06:10,420
She entered the house and greeted Elizabeth, and at the sound of Mary's greeting, Elizabeth's

83
00:06:10,420 --> 00:06:14,800
child leaped within her, and Elizabeth was filled with the Holy Spirit.

84
00:06:15,980 --> 00:06:21,460
Elizabeth gave a glad cry and exclaimed to Mary, you are blessed by God above all other

85
00:06:21,460 --> 00:06:23,660
women, and your child is blessed.

86
00:06:24,260 --> 00:06:28,180
What an honor this is that the mother of my Lord should visit me.

87
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:34,280
When you came in and greeted me, my baby jumped for joy the instant I heard your voice.

88
00:06:35,020 --> 00:06:39,800
You are blessed because you believe that the Lord would do what he said.

89
00:06:40,100 --> 00:06:48,220
I'd like for us now to step back and enter this world for a few moments.

90
00:06:49,700 --> 00:06:55,940
We read of the angel Gabriel who made a visit to this backwater town called Nazareth

91
00:06:55,940 --> 00:06:58,080
in the countryside of Galilee.

92
00:06:59,280 --> 00:07:01,040
It's not the kind of place

93
00:07:01,040 --> 00:07:03,740
where kings are supposed to come from.

94
00:07:04,630 --> 00:07:06,370
This is not the kind of place

95
00:07:06,370 --> 00:07:07,690
where the God of the universe

96
00:07:07,690 --> 00:07:09,770
is supposed to do His work.

97
00:07:11,820 --> 00:07:13,160
Maybe we can learn something

98
00:07:13,160 --> 00:07:14,920
about the humility of this scene.

99
00:07:15,260 --> 00:07:16,800
Perhaps God has a heart

100
00:07:16,800 --> 00:07:18,360
for doing the unexpected,

101
00:07:19,140 --> 00:07:20,720
for loving the unlovely,

102
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:26,630
for frequenting the lowly places there

103
00:07:26,630 --> 00:07:39,090
In this less than glamorous town, the angel of God visited a girl, a young teenage girl, Mary, engaged to a carpenter named Joseph.

104
00:07:40,430 --> 00:07:42,210
He came to bring her a message.

105
00:07:43,440 --> 00:07:45,500
Let's think about Mary for just a moment.

106
00:07:47,830 --> 00:07:50,610
Think back to when you were 15.

107
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:54,820
Can you go back that far?

108
00:07:56,930 --> 00:07:59,250
What were you doing at 15?

109
00:08:01,650 --> 00:08:03,810
Some of you have children here about 15.

110
00:08:03,810 --> 00:08:06,730
Some of you have grandchildren here, about 15.

111
00:08:08,610 --> 00:08:09,890
It's an awkward time, isn't it?

112
00:08:09,970 --> 00:08:10,430
15.

113
00:08:11,870 --> 00:08:14,830
Your body is somewhere between childhood and adulthood.

114
00:08:16,610 --> 00:08:19,570
Hormones are doing all kinds of crazy things to your body.

115
00:08:20,310 --> 00:08:22,270
And there's this desire to grow up.

116
00:08:24,640 --> 00:08:27,300
And at 15, not old enough to drive quite yet.

117
00:08:27,860 --> 00:08:30,860
Can't vote, can't stay out late, can't quite live on your own.

118
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:33,400
A lot of things you're not allowed to do.

119
00:08:37,130 --> 00:08:37,610
15.

120
00:08:39,560 --> 00:08:40,040
15.

121
00:08:40,040 --> 00:08:42,340
Think about what you're interested in at 15.

122
00:08:44,610 --> 00:08:47,710
And then imagine you hear a disturbance in the living room.

123
00:08:50,030 --> 00:09:00,510
You get up and you go downstairs, and there in your living room is this beautiful, supernatural, terrifying, angelic presence,

124
00:09:01,170 --> 00:09:04,810
radiating light and glory throughout your living room.

125
00:09:05,980 --> 00:09:07,960
And he speaks these words to you.

126
00:09:08,780 --> 00:09:12,020
Mary, you have nothing to fear.

127
00:09:13,320 --> 00:09:16,060
God has a surprise for you.

128
00:09:17,440 --> 00:09:20,040
You will become pregnant and give birth to a son

129
00:09:20,040 --> 00:09:21,780
and call his name Jesus.

130
00:09:24,020 --> 00:09:26,550
That is a surprise.

131
00:09:28,560 --> 00:09:32,140
That to me is one of those wonderful understatements in Scripture.

132
00:09:32,560 --> 00:09:34,060
I've got a surprise for you.

133
00:09:35,410 --> 00:09:38,230
You're going to become pregnant and you've never been with a man.

134
00:09:38,230 --> 00:09:39,810
Your whole life's going to change.

135
00:09:40,030 --> 00:09:40,430
Surprise!

136
00:09:45,210 --> 00:09:48,630
What's amazing to me is not only this holy moment,

137
00:09:48,630 --> 00:09:59,600
but Mary's response, her response reveals her character. For her to say, I am the Lord's servant

138
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:07,630
and I am willing to accept whatever he wants, that is no small statement. And though she is young,

139
00:10:07,630 --> 00:10:16,380
she is a very special, mature young lady because her entire life is about to change.

140
00:10:17,750 --> 00:10:20,590
Nothing will be the same for her.

141
00:10:21,960 --> 00:10:25,580
A few words from the angel, a few words from Mary's lips,

142
00:10:25,860 --> 00:10:28,180
and her world is never the same.

143
00:10:28,320 --> 00:10:29,480
We'll change it forever.

144
00:10:29,480 --> 00:10:34,480
And friends, because of these words, our world changes forever.

145
00:10:36,530 --> 00:10:37,830
Because of this scene.

146
00:10:40,400 --> 00:10:45,240
Do you think Mary, perhaps, was afraid of what was going to happen?

147
00:10:46,870 --> 00:10:47,330
I do.

148
00:10:48,840 --> 00:10:53,860
I think she bravely said, yes, Lord, whatever might come.

149
00:10:55,150 --> 00:11:03,010
But I think in her humanity, deep down, there's a pile of fears that might have been running through her head.

150
00:11:05,080 --> 00:11:06,460
Could be a fear of criticism.

151
00:11:07,850 --> 00:11:10,050
What is everybody going to think?

152
00:11:11,910 --> 00:11:12,850
This is a small town.

153
00:11:15,180 --> 00:11:16,880
This is small town life.

154
00:11:18,490 --> 00:11:19,490
Mary's pregnant, you hear?

155
00:11:19,490 --> 00:11:21,150
Oh my gosh, how did that happen?

156
00:11:22,920 --> 00:11:24,080
They're not even married yet.

157
00:11:24,080 --> 00:11:31,290
Can you imagine living with that in a small town 2,000 years ago?

158
00:11:33,470 --> 00:11:35,430
Perhaps a fear of the supernatural.

159
00:11:36,330 --> 00:11:37,670
What is going to happen to me?

160
00:11:38,910 --> 00:11:41,690
What do you mean the Holy Spirit is going to overshadow me?

161
00:11:44,720 --> 00:11:46,180
Perhaps she felt inadequate.

162
00:11:47,150 --> 00:11:50,200
How in the world am I going to handle this?

163
00:11:52,780 --> 00:11:55,700
Perhaps she was afraid of the changes she could see in her life.

164
00:11:55,920 --> 00:11:57,200
What will happen to my life?

165
00:11:57,260 --> 00:11:58,420
What's going to happen next?

166
00:12:01,990 --> 00:12:04,650
I bring up those fears that Mary has

167
00:12:04,650 --> 00:12:07,430
because you know they apply to us as well.

168
00:12:07,730 --> 00:12:10,290
Those are the same fears that we can have

169
00:12:10,290 --> 00:12:13,230
as we sit here on the eve of the next year.

170
00:12:13,730 --> 00:12:16,950
We sit here on the cusp of the 2004

171
00:12:16,950 --> 00:12:21,510
and friends, God wants to be a part of your life

172
00:12:21,510 --> 00:12:24,550
and to use you and do amazing things through you

173
00:12:24,550 --> 00:12:27,230
but you may be sitting here feeling the same thing.

174
00:12:27,550 --> 00:12:30,130
Fear of criticism, fear of the supernatural,

175
00:12:30,130 --> 00:12:33,190
fear of being inadequate, fear of change.

176
00:12:35,960 --> 00:12:37,180
What would people think?

177
00:12:37,580 --> 00:12:41,580
What would people think if I really committed to Jesus?

178
00:12:43,610 --> 00:12:46,130
They might think I'm a Jesus freak or something.

179
00:12:47,730 --> 00:12:48,310
Hallelujah.

180
00:12:48,870 --> 00:12:50,010
I like that.

181
00:12:51,950 --> 00:12:57,210
Because in our world, religion is a good thing in little pieces, at home, private.

182
00:12:58,890 --> 00:13:03,610
Heaven forbid you would actually live it out voraciously in your life.

183
00:13:03,610 --> 00:13:05,890
That would make you radical.

184
00:13:08,300 --> 00:13:09,640
And we don't want to be radical.

185
00:13:10,480 --> 00:13:12,180
We want to be respectable.

186
00:13:14,880 --> 00:13:19,520
What would people think if I really lived my life on the edge of faith?

187
00:13:21,900 --> 00:13:24,340
What could I really do for the Lord?

188
00:13:26,570 --> 00:13:29,610
And yes, how is this going to change my life?

189
00:13:29,930 --> 00:13:33,770
Because living on the edge with Jesus will change your life.

190
00:13:34,520 --> 00:13:35,560
That's a guarantee.

191
00:13:37,080 --> 00:13:39,080
And I have no idea what it will look like.

192
00:13:39,460 --> 00:13:40,860
And neither do you.

193
00:13:40,940 --> 00:13:44,580
but that's where life was meant to be lived.

194
00:13:45,040 --> 00:13:46,620
As that illustration we've talked about,

195
00:13:46,660 --> 00:13:48,700
it's grabbing onto the coattails of Jesus

196
00:13:48,700 --> 00:13:52,400
and just holding on as he takes you on a journey

197
00:13:52,400 --> 00:13:53,880
you could never imagine.

198
00:13:54,300 --> 00:13:56,220
That's where life gets really interesting.

199
00:13:58,470 --> 00:14:00,370
Some have called it the purpose-driven life,

200
00:14:01,330 --> 00:14:03,770
a life where God's purpose is alive in you

201
00:14:03,770 --> 00:14:06,550
as you hold onto him, as he takes you where he wants.

202
00:14:06,910 --> 00:14:09,050
Can you imagine living that kind of life?

203
00:14:09,770 --> 00:14:12,430
Are you ready to live that kind of life?

204
00:14:12,430 --> 00:14:17,970
If the Bible says, don't be afraid, the angel said to Mary, in fact, he's saying to us,

205
00:14:18,050 --> 00:14:23,320
don't be afraid, I want to do some things with you if you'll let me.

206
00:14:25,830 --> 00:14:30,830
And remember this, nothing is impossible with God.

207
00:14:33,910 --> 00:14:37,610
It's one thing to read it, it's another thing to live it.

208
00:14:38,010 --> 00:14:39,750
Nothing is impossible with God.

209
00:14:39,750 --> 00:14:44,510
If he wants to do something in your life, will you trust him to do it and surrender to him?

210
00:14:44,510 --> 00:14:48,160
for nothing is impossible with God.

211
00:14:52,220 --> 00:14:53,360
Mary trusts God.

212
00:14:55,150 --> 00:14:57,270
She trusts God in the face of difficulty.

213
00:14:57,550 --> 00:14:59,710
She trusts God in the face of perilous

214
00:14:59,710 --> 00:15:00,990
and an uncertain future.

215
00:15:01,510 --> 00:15:03,990
She trusts God in the face of challenges

216
00:15:03,990 --> 00:15:06,050
and changes.

217
00:15:07,870 --> 00:15:09,890
Church, can we hear that today?

218
00:15:10,990 --> 00:15:13,410
Can you hear deep in your soul

219
00:15:13,410 --> 00:15:16,370
that nothing is impossible with God?

220
00:15:19,010 --> 00:15:21,630
If God is calling you to something new,

221
00:15:21,630 --> 00:15:24,310
he will empower you to do it.

222
00:15:25,140 --> 00:15:27,700
If God wants to change something in your life,

223
00:15:27,920 --> 00:15:30,500
he will give you the resources to do it.

224
00:15:30,700 --> 00:15:34,020
If God has you facing some real challenges and difficulties,

225
00:15:34,360 --> 00:15:39,000
he is with you, for nothing is impossible with God.

226
00:15:40,060 --> 00:15:40,340
Amen?

227
00:15:42,660 --> 00:15:44,160
Can we hear this today?

228
00:15:46,600 --> 00:15:51,160
And if we hear it, will we be obedient unto God?

229
00:15:55,530 --> 00:15:57,310
Mary says, okay, let's go.

230
00:15:58,620 --> 00:15:59,600
Be it as you may.

231
00:16:00,710 --> 00:16:06,870
She chooses obedience and trust over disobedience and fear.

232
00:16:08,870 --> 00:16:11,450
She could have let her fears overtake her.

233
00:16:13,150 --> 00:16:17,590
She could have chosen to ignore what the angel said and say, I'm not involved in this.

234
00:16:18,660 --> 00:16:20,540
I don't do the supernatural thing.

235
00:16:22,160 --> 00:16:23,540
I like my wedding coming up.

236
00:16:23,600 --> 00:16:25,040
I like it just the way it is.

237
00:16:25,840 --> 00:16:26,580
No thank you.

238
00:16:26,900 --> 00:16:31,920
She chose to trust and be obedient.

239
00:16:32,840 --> 00:16:38,300
She chose to embrace what God was up to, even if it's personally uncomfortable for her,

240
00:16:39,880 --> 00:16:43,660
because she wants God's purposes more than her own.

241
00:16:45,390 --> 00:16:48,210
And she believes with God that all things are possible.

242
00:16:48,630 --> 00:16:54,770
And notice, as the text continues, not only does she become pregnant,

243
00:16:55,090 --> 00:17:00,490
but an old barren woman, her relative Elizabeth, can suddenly bear a child as well.

244
00:17:00,490 --> 00:17:07,700
and God is about to enter into human history as a child.

245
00:17:08,280 --> 00:17:11,080
Nothing is impossible with God.

246
00:17:14,670 --> 00:17:16,310
And later through Jesus' life,

247
00:17:16,470 --> 00:17:18,110
we're going to see that from a tomb

248
00:17:18,110 --> 00:17:21,070
can come resurrection and life.

249
00:17:21,070 --> 00:17:23,490
We're going to see eventually the Holy Spirit

250
00:17:23,490 --> 00:17:24,710
coming into the world.

251
00:17:24,890 --> 00:17:27,710
We're going to see a church born where there was none.

252
00:17:27,970 --> 00:17:29,970
We're going to see people all over the world

253
00:17:29,970 --> 00:17:32,150
transformed by the power of the Spirit.

254
00:17:32,630 --> 00:17:35,010
Nothing is impossible with God.

255
00:17:37,850 --> 00:17:39,270
Church, are we listening?

256
00:17:40,160 --> 00:17:40,980
Are we listening?

257
00:17:44,750 --> 00:17:48,890
Emmanuel means God with us.

258
00:17:50,700 --> 00:17:55,200
Nothing is impossible when God is with us.

259
00:17:57,280 --> 00:18:00,360
Are you ready to live in 2004

260
00:18:00,360 --> 00:18:04,360
this reality of Emmanuel, God with you?

261
00:18:04,360 --> 00:18:14,990
It's quite an encounter she has, isn't it?

262
00:18:17,330 --> 00:18:20,570
And after this amazing encounter with the angel,

263
00:18:21,760 --> 00:18:25,540
Mary travels to see her relative Elizabeth.

264
00:18:26,040 --> 00:18:28,880
Three-day journey, possibly five-day journey.

265
00:18:30,750 --> 00:18:35,290
And when she arrives at Elizabeth's home, she enters and greets her.

266
00:18:35,410 --> 00:18:36,330
And I love this.

267
00:18:36,330 --> 00:18:49,440
The baby in Elizabeth's womb leaped within her, excited about the presence of the child being formed in Mary's womb.

268
00:18:50,890 --> 00:18:53,450
There's something about being in the presence of Jesus

269
00:18:53,450 --> 00:18:56,430
that invites a reaction in our very souls.

270
00:18:56,750 --> 00:18:58,390
That baby leaped within the womb.

271
00:19:00,090 --> 00:19:00,890
And you know who that is?

272
00:19:00,930 --> 00:19:01,950
It's John the Baptist.

273
00:19:04,140 --> 00:19:05,260
We'll see him later.

274
00:19:08,250 --> 00:19:09,730
John the Baptist in utero,

275
00:19:09,910 --> 00:19:11,350
sensing the presence of God,

276
00:19:11,590 --> 00:19:12,950
and he leaps in the womb.

277
00:19:14,630 --> 00:19:17,010
Friends, when we experience the power of Jesus,

278
00:19:17,130 --> 00:19:18,550
the very presence of Jesus,

279
00:19:18,950 --> 00:19:20,250
there's something inside of us

280
00:19:20,250 --> 00:19:21,770
that must cry out in worship.

281
00:19:21,770 --> 00:19:23,690
We must leap for joy

282
00:19:23,690 --> 00:19:29,350
Because the Lord has come, and that's what Christmas is all about.

283
00:19:33,550 --> 00:19:36,190
Will you leap in your own way?

284
00:19:36,870 --> 00:19:39,350
Will you really worship this season?

285
00:19:39,870 --> 00:19:42,410
Jesus come, God in the flesh.

286
00:19:42,750 --> 00:19:50,040
Will you really let go and abandon yourselves to love and to worship this baby that's come

287
00:19:50,040 --> 00:19:50,960
to save you?

288
00:19:51,400 --> 00:19:54,330
In your own way, will you leap for joy?

289
00:19:56,260 --> 00:19:57,080
And that's the question.

290
00:19:57,840 --> 00:20:02,000
What is our response to this child?

291
00:20:04,840 --> 00:20:07,800
Amidst all the changes, all the challenges,

292
00:20:09,360 --> 00:20:13,340
amidst all the personal struggles or pains or hurts you might have experienced,

293
00:20:13,340 --> 00:20:16,360
or perhaps amidst all the good times and the blessings,

294
00:20:16,760 --> 00:20:23,530
will you respond as John did to the very presence of Jesus?

295
00:20:24,270 --> 00:20:28,930
Will you leap for joy that Christ has come this holiday Christmas season?

296
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:31,860
Will you leap for joy?

297
00:20:33,870 --> 00:20:37,130
As we've talked about in weeks past, joy is a gift of God.

298
00:20:37,290 --> 00:20:41,250
It's rooted in a strong, intimate relationship with our loving Lord.

299
00:20:41,790 --> 00:20:44,250
It doesn't always mean that you're happy all the time,

300
00:20:44,250 --> 00:20:49,210
but it means there's a confidence in the God who is for you and with you.

301
00:20:50,580 --> 00:20:53,740
And there's nothing like that experience in the world.

302
00:20:54,920 --> 00:20:57,820
All the fun things in the world, all the drugs in the world,

303
00:20:57,960 --> 00:20:59,240
all the free love in the world,

304
00:20:59,240 --> 00:21:03,480
all the things the world pursues with a vengeance

305
00:21:03,480 --> 00:21:07,580
is nothing compared to the power and the presence

306
00:21:07,580 --> 00:21:10,840
and the joy of God with us.

307
00:21:14,280 --> 00:21:15,620
Nothing's impossible with God.

308
00:21:18,600 --> 00:21:21,060
So church, will you worship God and love Him

309
00:21:21,060 --> 00:21:22,440
and enjoy God forever?

310
00:21:23,180 --> 00:21:25,320
In the midst of whatever you're facing,

311
00:21:25,520 --> 00:21:28,460
challenges, changes, whatever it is,

312
00:21:30,560 --> 00:21:34,540
will you love God with your heart, soul, mind, and strength?

313
00:21:36,450 --> 00:21:38,530
Can you see God's hand in your life

314
00:21:38,530 --> 00:21:41,630
in the midst of all this chaos and uncertainty of our world?

315
00:21:41,930 --> 00:21:43,850
Can you see Him moving now

316
00:21:43,850 --> 00:21:47,620
and want to take you to new heights, new places,

317
00:21:48,180 --> 00:21:50,300
new places to grow?

318
00:21:52,810 --> 00:21:56,230
Can you trust that God is with you?

319
00:21:57,700 --> 00:21:58,520
Do you believe it?

320
00:22:00,680 --> 00:22:02,860
Not only do you believe it in church and say amen,

321
00:22:03,000 --> 00:22:04,800
but do you believe it Monday and Tuesday

322
00:22:04,800 --> 00:22:07,000
and Wednesday and Thursday and so on?

323
00:22:07,000 --> 00:22:09,120
eight days a week.

324
00:22:09,700 --> 00:22:10,440
Do you believe it?

325
00:22:14,780 --> 00:22:17,700
Can you believe that God has a special call in your life

326
00:22:17,700 --> 00:22:19,080
to do something great for Him?

327
00:22:21,260 --> 00:22:23,200
Can you believe He's given you gifts

328
00:22:23,200 --> 00:22:24,540
that He wants to do ministry

329
00:22:24,540 --> 00:22:28,420
and He wants to have you pursue things in this world

330
00:22:28,420 --> 00:22:30,440
that people might know that He's alive?

331
00:22:30,680 --> 00:22:32,560
He wants to stretch you and grow you.

332
00:22:32,780 --> 00:22:33,760
Can you believe it?

333
00:22:33,920 --> 00:22:35,380
Nothing is impossible with God.

334
00:22:36,800 --> 00:22:37,720
Can you hear this?

335
00:22:38,440 --> 00:22:40,080
Are you ready to live 2004

336
00:22:40,080 --> 00:22:45,020
like it's the last year alive.

337
00:22:47,270 --> 00:22:49,030
As we talked about a few weeks ago,

338
00:22:49,130 --> 00:22:50,870
we don't know when the end has come.

339
00:22:50,870 --> 00:22:54,790
Can we live as if each day is precious unto the Lord

340
00:22:54,790 --> 00:22:56,630
and as if He really is with you?

341
00:22:56,670 --> 00:23:01,450
Because He is with that kind of vitality

342
00:23:01,450 --> 00:23:05,290
and focus and purpose.

343
00:23:08,410 --> 00:23:10,330
Even if it's not easy, will you do it?

344
00:23:11,160 --> 00:23:12,460
It wasn't easy for Mary.

345
00:23:14,880 --> 00:23:18,100
This story looks sweet in a Hallmark store, doesn't it?

346
00:23:20,420 --> 00:23:23,440
I love buying and putting up that little crash scene.

347
00:23:23,540 --> 00:23:26,900
It's sweet, it's tender, it kind of pulls on the strings.

348
00:23:27,220 --> 00:23:31,520
But you know, in reality, it was dank and dark and smelly and difficult.

349
00:23:35,400 --> 00:23:40,060
You see, 2,000 years, we can cleanse it and sanitize it, but it was a messy, dirty reality.

350
00:23:40,060 --> 00:23:45,480
But that's God entering into our real, messy, dirty, broken world.

351
00:23:48,820 --> 00:23:53,220
And Jesus experienced every challenge, every temptation that we experience.

352
00:23:53,220 --> 00:23:56,440
this is not a God who is removed and distant

353
00:23:56,440 --> 00:23:59,480
this is a God who has walked in your shoes

354
00:23:59,480 --> 00:24:05,220
some of you were born at St. Jude

355
00:24:05,220 --> 00:24:11,840
with clean white sheets

356
00:24:11,840 --> 00:24:16,300
and machines and all kinds of good things around

357
00:24:16,300 --> 00:24:17,780
to sustain life

358
00:24:17,780 --> 00:24:23,020
our Savior was born in a stable, in a cave

359
00:24:23,020 --> 00:24:25,460
and put in a manger, a trough

360
00:24:25,460 --> 00:24:26,880
for animals

361
00:24:26,880 --> 00:24:31,920
this was not an easy scene

362
00:24:37,200 --> 00:24:39,780
No painkillers for Mary's birth.

363
00:24:42,540 --> 00:24:44,840
No tender place to place the child.

364
00:24:47,280 --> 00:24:53,430
The ridicule, the challenges, the uncertain future of what she says.

365
00:24:53,610 --> 00:24:55,910
Yes, Lord, whatever you want.

366
00:24:56,190 --> 00:24:57,710
Your purpose is above mine.

367
00:24:57,910 --> 00:24:58,870
I trust you.

368
00:24:59,230 --> 00:25:01,710
Yes, Emmanuel, you are with me.

369
00:25:01,970 --> 00:25:02,730
I'll do it.

370
00:25:03,700 --> 00:25:05,320
Can that be our story as well?

371
00:25:05,720 --> 00:25:09,360
I get motivated by this 15-year-old girl.

372
00:25:11,200 --> 00:25:12,440
Oh, ministry is so hard.

373
00:25:12,440 --> 00:25:19,560
I'm really stuck, I'm challenged, or whatever's going on, Mary said, yes, Lord, your business

374
00:25:19,560 --> 00:25:24,220
might be struggling, your home life might be difficult, but can we say, yes, Lord, you're

375
00:25:24,220 --> 00:25:33,400
with me, and take our cue from a 15-year-old in a backwater town where God did something

376
00:25:33,400 --> 00:25:33,920
special.

377
00:25:37,940 --> 00:25:40,220
So will you trust Jesus this Christmas season?

378
00:25:41,300 --> 00:25:45,220
Will you worship him with full abandonment, give him your best, give him your all, give

379
00:25:45,220 --> 00:25:51,850
him your very will, that you might allow him to do what he's calling in your life.

380
00:25:53,580 --> 00:25:57,000
And if you will, 2004 will be unlike anything you've ever seen.

381
00:25:58,300 --> 00:26:02,180
And my prayer is it'll be a great, growing, stretching year as you learn to trust him

382
00:26:02,180 --> 00:26:08,660
each and every day, and that each day will be lived as an adventure before God, who is

383
00:26:08,660 --> 00:26:11,920
Emmanuel, God with us.

384
00:26:12,820 --> 00:26:13,440
Let's pray.

385
00:26:13,540 --> 00:26:16,230
Lord, thank you for your power.

386
00:26:16,230 --> 00:26:18,500
thank you that there

387
00:26:18,500 --> 00:26:21,400
is nothing that can't be accomplished

388
00:26:21,400 --> 00:26:23,420
through you and by your power

389
00:26:23,420 --> 00:26:27,150
as we pray frequently

390
00:26:27,150 --> 00:26:29,490
in this church may these not just be words

391
00:26:29,490 --> 00:26:31,050
but be realities

392
00:26:31,050 --> 00:26:33,030
that we take deep within us

393
00:26:33,030 --> 00:26:36,210
that we chew on them and ingest

394
00:26:36,210 --> 00:26:38,290
them and make them part of us

395
00:26:38,290 --> 00:26:42,950
so Lord may we give our

396
00:26:42,950 --> 00:26:44,350
total all in all to you

397
00:26:44,350 --> 00:26:48,820
and Lord may 2004

398
00:26:48,820 --> 00:26:51,150
be a year

399
00:26:51,150 --> 00:26:54,190
of real growth

400
00:26:54,190 --> 00:26:57,890
a real year of trusting you

401
00:26:57,890 --> 00:26:58,850
in new things

402
00:26:58,850 --> 00:27:00,770
letting you have parts of us

403
00:27:00,770 --> 00:27:01,770
we've never given you

404
00:27:01,770 --> 00:27:04,600
seeing your hand at work

405
00:27:04,600 --> 00:27:06,540
as we live in dependence

406
00:27:06,540 --> 00:27:07,900
day in and day out

407
00:27:07,900 --> 00:27:10,170
on your Holy Spirit

408
00:27:10,170 --> 00:27:12,980
we pray there would be ministry

409
00:27:12,980 --> 00:27:14,440
that would flow out of us

410
00:27:14,440 --> 00:27:16,950
there would be power and love

411
00:27:16,950 --> 00:27:19,910
and trust that just pour forth

412
00:27:19,910 --> 00:27:22,310
from a heart that is filled up with you

413
00:27:22,310 --> 00:27:28,300
so Lord we commit this coming year

414
00:27:28,300 --> 00:27:31,170
to living in a spirit of Mary

415
00:27:31,170 --> 00:27:43,270
that says, be as it may, may your will be done on earth as it is in heaven. That's our prayer.

416
00:27:45,360 --> 00:27:53,120
Lord, may this be a very special Christmas season. Lord, may we as the church be family

417
00:27:53,120 --> 00:28:02,110
at this time. Be there for each other. May we see in each other, Emmanuel, God with us.

418
00:28:03,480 --> 00:28:10,600
And may each of us encourage the other to live a life of worship, abandonment, and trust.

419
00:28:10,600 --> 00:28:14,610
with a God who says nothing is impossible with him.

420
00:28:17,620 --> 00:28:19,120
And may that be our story as well.

421
00:28:21,440 --> 00:28:24,800
In Christ's precious, powerful name, amen.

422
00:28:26,760 --> 00:28:27,420
I'm going to stand.

423
00:28:27,500 --> 00:28:28,740
We're going to sing a couple songs.

